  "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\nWhen users receive notifications and they open the AC, they have no way to tell which tab the notification belongs. They have two cumbersome alternatives:\r\n\r\n- Open the `All` tab and search for the new unread notification. This is okay for most users, but the ones with lots of notifications of varying types can find the process tedious.\r\n- Open each tab until the desired notification is visible and the user can decide what to do about it.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\n\r\n- Show the unread badge on each tab containing one or more unread notifications.\r\n- The badge should disappear if there are no unread notifications.\r\n- Don't show the badge on the `All` tab.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/213873286-1647a8df-fe7f-4dd3-aab4-554d13ec3966.png\" width=\"400\" />\r\n\r\n## References\r\n\r\n- https://www.figma.com/file/eDfxTa9IoaCMUy5cLTp0ys/Shell-for-Mobile?node-id=451%3A18681&t=wwEILzdU13eKAvtW-0",
